AGI -&nbsp;The name of Francis was the 15-month-old child who died after being killed by two pitbulls. The tregedia was consumed this morning in the locality Campolongo di Eboli, in Salernitano. According to a first reconstruction, the attack on the part of the two dogs took place inside the house, on the arrival of the health care of the 118 the little more than a year had already died.
&nbsp;
The child &nbsp;<b> was in arm to an uncle</b>, ready to go out of the house, when it was reached by dogs just outside the door. The two pitbulls hurled against the little boy and snatched him. The man remained unharmed, while the mother was injured in the attack. When he realized what was going on, &nbsp;<b> tried to save his son</b>, tearing him from the fury of the two dogs that turned against him.&nbsp; The woman was medicated on the spot by the health. In the two-storey villa, the reliefs and investigations of the Carabinieri of the Company of Eboli continue under the coordination of the Procura di Salerno. On the spot, pm and medical examiner.
&nbsp;
&nbsp; "A disgrace that softens the entire city", we read in a social post of the Municipality of Eboli. "Our community is deeply shaken by the immense tragedy that occurred this morning in Campolongo. The attack of two pitbulls has torn to life a child of just 15 months under the horrified eyes of the mother, also wounded. To the relatives of the little Francis we make our deep mourning simple, know that the words, in such cases, can hardly relieve the pain", is added in the post signed by the mayor and the municipal administration.
